    • initialize

      public void initialize()
      Initialises and starts the game with the level 1 from cold.

    • startLevel

      public void startLevel​(java.lang.String fileName, int delay)
      Constructs and draws the game level by considering the text file. Adds the necessary blocks , players, enemies , powerups, lasers in the level scene. Starting points for every character is set.
      Parameters:
      fileName - for the game level that should be displayer for player.
      delay - time after a level finishes and before a new level starts.

    • startNewGame

      public void startNewGame()
      Create a stub and cold start of the game. Initialises all values to the starting values. Called everytime a game started.

    • startNextLevel

      public void startNextLevel()
      Create a next level of the game after first level completes.. Initialises all values to the starting values. Called everytime a previous level finishes.

    • step

      public void step()
      Counts the steps of player and enemies. Each move is a step indeed. At each step verifies the state of the game and collect the power-ups, coins and execute methods. Decides the player dead scenarios. And enemies scattering positions in a quadrant basis for smoothening enemy AI moves.

    • shoot

      public void shoot​(ShipModel ship)
      Function that implements shooting mechanism . Shooting while it sets the location of player and direction.
      Parameters:
      ship - selected that implements shoot mechanism.

    • handle

      public void handle​(javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent keyEvent)
      Controls the player movement. Implements two way keyboard controls for player.
      Specified by:
      handle in interface javafx.event.EventHandler<javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent>
      Parameters:
      keyEvent - gets the jkeys pressed by player

    • createLifeHBox

      public void createLifeHBox()
      Creates the HBox for player lives. Reduces by 1 image each time player dies. Increased by 1 image each time player collects the life coin

    • createBulletBox

      public void createBulletBox()
      Creates the HBox for bullet count that to be shot by player. Reduces by 1 image each time player shoots a bullet. Increased by 1 image each time player collects the power-up coin.

    • createPauseScene

      public void createPauseScene()
      Method create and initialises the pause sub scene flaring up when player wants to pause. Sets the five option buttons and displaying necessary info when pressed. Resume, New Game, Settings, Help and Exit buttons are created. It extends the functionality of typical button classes defined. And also the actions represents and constrained to one game.

    • pause

      public void pause()
      Function that stops the timer and pauses the game.
